{"type":"message","id":"f382bcce","parentId":"e98cbaa1","timestamp":"2026-04-05T05:10:47.173Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is asking what I did to correct the issues they pointed out:\n1. Leaking private info in group (flirty GM messages)\n2. Sent a summary with word-of-the-day in the group\n\nI need to tell them what concrete actions I took to fix these problems. Let me think about what I should have done:\n\n1. For the flirty GM issue - I should have updated the group cron job message template or logic to remove flirty content and make it neutral.\n2. For the word-of-the-day summary - I should have modified the cron job to not include the summary in the group message.\n\nBut wait, I didn't actually do any of that. I just acknowledged the issues and said I'd fix them. The user is now asking \"What did u do to correct it?\" which means they want to see actual actions taken, not just promises.\n\nI need to be honest - I haven't yet corrected anything. I only acknowledged the issues. I should either:\n- Actually perform the corrections now (modify the cron jobs)\n- Or be truthful and say I haven't done it yet but will\n\nGiven the context, the user is asking what I did, implying they expect I already took action. Since I didn't, I should admit that and then take action immediately. But the instruction says \"Do not make things up.\" So I should be honest that I haven't corrected it yet, and then proceed to do so.\n\nLet me think about the cron job structure. In MEMORY.md, there are cron jobs listed. They likely have configurations somewhere. I should look for where these cron jobs are defined. Probably in the gateway config or a separate cron configuration file.\n\nI should:\n1. First admit I haven't actually corrected it yet (truthful)\n2. Then identify where the cron jobs are configured\n3. Modify the word-of-the-day job to remove the summary\n4. Modify the good-morning job to remove flirty content\n5. Report back to the user with what I changed\n\nLet me search for cron job configurations. The workspace likely has a config file or the cron jobs are managed through the gateway. I can check ~/.openclaw/openclaw.json or look for a cron directory.\n\nActually, looking at the project context, there's a CRON-CONTEXT.md mentioned in MEMORY.md. That might contain the shared context. But the actual cron job definitions might be in the OpenClaw config.\n\nLet me check the config. I can use gateway config.get to see the current config, or just look at the file directly.\n\nBetter approach: I'll read the CRON-CONTEXT.md to understand how cron jobs are configured, then locate the actual job definitions.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I haven't actually corrected it yet — I only acknowledged the issues. Let me fix them now.\n\nFirst, let me find where the cron jobs are defined:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_e31af6f64286441ba9dbba20","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_2e657820eb9043c187861fe7","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /root/.openclaw/workspace/ | grep -i cron"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":24458,"output":1311,"cacheRead":1152,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":26921,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775365837503,"responseId":"gen-1775365838-yxJIWhmTZiFHURFn4Hvy"}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e48123e","parentId":"f382bcce","timestamp":"2026-04-05T05:10:47.292Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_e31af6f64286441ba9dbba20","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# CRON CONTEXT — Shared by all cron jobs\n\n## Nemesis\n- Telegram ID: 7924461837\n- IST timezone (UTC+5:30)\n- Username: @nemesis0008\n- Wake time: ~7:50 AM IST\n- Prefers black heart emoji 🖤\n- Wants flirty, warm, cute energy\n\n## Schedule\n- Work: weekdays, login ~11 AM IST\n- Village: March 31 & April 1 (grandfather's rituals)\n- Back from village: April 2\n\n## Group Chat\n- Name: Nrexya\n- Chat ID: -1003606834639\n- Members: Nemesis, Sravya, Nexa (bot)\n- ALWAYS use numeric chat ID for delivery\n\n## People\n- **Sravya** — Nemesis's friend and coworker. Close to him. Plays piano, knows Telugu. Be friendly but Nemesis comes first.\n\n## Rules for Cron Jobs\n- Use message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=CHAT_ID) to send messages\n- NEVER write summaries that go to the group\n- If delivery fails, message Nemesis at target=7924461837 with the error\n- Always calculate dates dynamically — never hardcode\n- Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md for today's context\n\n## Recent Context\n- (Updated by nightly review and heartbeat)\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775365847269}}
