{"type":"message","id":"20c61b9c","parentId":"a0dc5725","timestamp":"2026-04-05T06:17:36.656Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Ah, this skill is specifically for saving to Obsidian and is triggered by Japanese phrases like \"セッション終了\" (session end). That's very specific and not really what we need for our OpenClaw setup. The suspicious flag might be because it tries to access a hardcoded vault path.\n\nThis isn't the right fit for us. Let's skip it and try something else. Maybe `session-wrap-up`? Or maybe we're done with session-related skills and should look at process automation? Actually, we've already got `session-logs` and `session-cleanup` which are solid upgrades.\n\nLet me think about what else could improve our process:\n- We already have memory search working well\n- We have cron-health-check\n- We could use something for GitHub sync? Already have that.\n\nMaybe we should look at something for group chat interactions? Let's search for \"group\" or \"chat\" related skills.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"This one's too Obsidian-specific and expects Japanese trigger phrases. Not a fit for our setup. Let's try **session-wrap-up** instead — sounds more general:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_48ff1aeb866f439294f3e2de","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect session-wrap-up --files"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":678,"output":484,"cacheRead":48000,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49162,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775369849424,"responseId":"gen-1775369850-QlgW5tVAd8kYWLwucfk1"}}
{"type":"message","id":"1b40e4b3","parentId":"20c61b9c","timestamp":"2026-04-05T06:17:38.508Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_48ff1aeb866f439294f3e2de","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\nsession-wrap-up  Session Wrap-Up\nSummary: Wrap up a conversation session before starting a new one. Use when the user says \"wrap up\", \"wrap up this conversation\", \"session wrap up\", or uses /session_wrap_up command. Flushes context to memory files, updates PARA notes, commits changes, and provides a summary.\nOwner: branexp\nCreated: 2026-02-06T20:04:13.837Z\nUpdated: 2026-04-05T03:33:05.383Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nLicense: MIT-0 (Free to use, modify, and redistribute. No attribution required.)\nTags: latest=1.0.0\nSelected: 1.0.0\nSelected At: 2026-02-06T20:04:13.837Z\nChangelog: Initial release\nSecurity: SUSPICIOUS\nWarnings: yes\nChecked: 2026-04-05T03:33:05.202Z\nModel: gpt-5-mini\nFiles:\nSKILL.md  2.6KB  522469a89dfda4d27129a8588e9484f66deb55056ccfdf4dad9a5915fce108f1  text/markdown"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1831,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\nsession-wrap-up  Session Wrap-Up\nSummary: Wrap up a conversation session before starting a new one. Use when the user says \"wrap up\", \"wrap up this conversation\", \"session wrap up\", or uses /session_wrap_up command. Flushes context to memory files, updates PARA notes, commits changes, and provides a summary.\nOwner: branexp\nCreated: 2026-02-06T20:04:13.837Z\nUpdated: 2026-04-05T03:33:05.383Z\nLatest: 1.0.0\nLicense: MIT-0 (Free to use, modify, and redistribute. No attribution required.)\nTags: latest=1.0.0\nSelected: 1.0.0\nSelected At: 2026-02-06T20:04:13.837Z\nChangelog: Initial release\nSecurity: SUSPICIOUS\nWarnings: yes\nChecked: 2026-04-05T03:33:05.202Z\nModel: gpt-5-mini\nFiles:\nSKILL.md  2.6KB  522469a89dfda4d27129a8588e9484f66deb55056ccfdf4dad9a5915fce108f1  text/markdown","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775369858497}}
{"type":"message","id":"abebc9e5","parentId":"1b40e4b3","timestamp":"2026-04-05T06:17:42.421Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me check this one. It sounds like it might be more general-purpose. Suspicious flag again, but let's see what it does.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_b7bc9c8e294e48e09d7f8058","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"clawhub inspect session-wrap-up --file SKILL.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":849,"output":95,"cacheRead":48384,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":49328,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775369858508,"responseId":"gen-1775369859-HvgRIfghZleNustsnjIu"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7c0945f7","parentId":"abebc9e5","timestamp":"2026-04-05T06:17:44.485Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_b7bc9c8e294e48e09d7f8058","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"- Fetching skill\n---\nname: session-wrap-up\ndescription: Wrap up a conversation session before starting a new one. Use when the user says \"wrap up\", \"wrap up this conversation\", \"session wrap up\", or uses /session_wrap_up command. Flushes context to memory files, updates PARA notes, commits changes, and provides a summary.\n---\n\n# Session Wrap Up\n\nEnd-of-session protocol to preserve context and ensure continuity between sessions.\n\n## When Triggered\n\nRun this protocol when the user indicates they want to wrap up the current session before starting a new one.\n\n## Protocol Steps\n\nExecute these steps in order:\n\n### 1. Flush to Daily Log\n\nWrite to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create if doesn't exist):\n- Key topics discussed in this session\n- Decisions made\n- Commands, configs, or code that worked\n- Problems solved and how they were solved\n- Any gotchas or lessons learned\n\n### 2. Update Long-Term Memory\n\nIf significant learnings occurred, update `MEMORY.md`:\n- New user preferences discovered\n- Important lessons learned\n- Long-term decisions made\n- Workflow changes\n\n### 3. Update PARA Notes\n\nCheck and update the PARA structure in `notes/` (or `memory/notes/`):\n- **Open loops** (`notes/areas/open-loops.md`): Add new unfinished items, mark completed items with ✅\n- **Projects** (`notes/projects/`): Update progress on active projects\n- **Areas** (`notes/areas/`): Add new ongoing responsibilities\n- **Resources** (`notes/resources/`): Add new reference material, how-tos\n\n### 4. Commit Changes\n\n```bash\ncd <workspace>\ngit add -A\ngit status\ngit commit -m \"wrap-up: YYYY-MM-DD session summary\"\ngit push\n```\n\nNotes:\n- The wrap-up `git push` is **automatic** (no confirmation prompt).\n- If `git push` fails, report the error and leave the commit locally.\n\n### 5. Report Summary\n\nProvide a brief summary to the user:\n- What was captured\n- Files updated\n- Any items that need follow-up next session\n- Confirmation that changes were committed (and pushed, if successful)\n\n## Example Output\n\n```\n## Session Wrap-Up Complete ✅\n\n**Captured to daily log:**\n- Configured PARA second brain\n- Fixed vector indexing for notes\n- Set up weekly memory review cron\n\n**Updated:**\n- MEMORY.md: Added memory system learnings\n- notes/areas/open-loops.md: Marked .gitignore task complete\n\n**Committed:** `wrap-up: 2026-01-30 session summary`\n\n**Follow-up next session:**\n- Check LanceDB autoCapture setting\n- Consider morning briefing cron\n\nReady for new session! ⚡\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Always create the daily log file if it doesn't exist\n- Use the current date for filenames and commit messages\n- Keep summaries concise but complete\n- Include the ⚡ emoji at the end (GigaBot signature)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2030,"aggregated":"- Fetching skill\n---\nname: session-wrap-up\ndescription: Wrap up a conversation session before starting a new one. Use when the user says \"wrap up\", \"wrap up this conversation\", \"session wrap up\", or uses /session_wrap_up command. Flushes context to memory files, updates PARA notes, commits changes, and provides a summary.\n---\n\n# Session Wrap Up\n\nEnd-of-session protocol to preserve context and ensure continuity between sessions.\n\n## When Triggered\n\nRun this protocol when the user indicates they want to wrap up the current session before starting a new one.\n\n## Protocol Steps\n\nExecute these steps in order:\n\n### 1. Flush to Daily Log\n\nWrite to `memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md` (create if doesn't exist):\n- Key topics discussed in this session\n- Decisions made\n- Commands, configs, or code that worked\n- Problems solved and how they were solved\n- Any gotchas or lessons learned\n\n### 2. Update Long-Term Memory\n\nIf significant learnings occurred, update `MEMORY.md`:\n- New user preferences discovered\n- Important lessons learned\n- Long-term decisions made\n- Workflow changes\n\n### 3. Update PARA Notes\n\nCheck and update the PARA structure in `notes/` (or `memory/notes/`):\n- **Open loops** (`notes/areas/open-loops.md`): Add new unfinished items, mark completed items with ✅\n- **Projects** (`notes/projects/`): Update progress on active projects\n- **Areas** (`notes/areas/`): Add new ongoing responsibilities\n- **Resources** (`notes/resources/`): Add new reference material, how-tos\n\n### 4. Commit Changes\n\n```bash\ncd <workspace>\ngit add -A\ngit status\ngit commit -m \"wrap-up: YYYY-MM-DD session summary\"\ngit push\n```\n\nNotes:\n- The wrap-up `git push` is **automatic** (no confirmation prompt).\n- If `git push` fails, report the error and leave the commit locally.\n\n### 5. Report Summary\n\nProvide a brief summary to the user:\n- What was captured\n- Files updated\n- Any items that need follow-up next session\n- Confirmation that changes were committed (and pushed, if successful)\n\n## Example Output\n\n```\n## Session Wrap-Up Complete ✅\n\n**Captured to daily log:**\n- Configured PARA second brain\n- Fixed vector indexing for notes\n- Set up weekly memory review cron\n\n**Updated:**\n- MEMORY.md: Added memory system learnings\n- notes/areas/open-loops.md: Marked .gitignore task complete\n\n**Committed:** `wrap-up: 2026-01-30 session summary`\n\n**Follow-up next session:**\n- Check LanceDB autoCapture setting\n- Consider morning briefing cron\n\nReady for new session! ⚡\n```\n\n## Notes\n\n- Always create the daily log file if it doesn't exist\n- Use the current date for filenames and commit messages\n- Keep summaries concise but complete\n- Include the ⚡ emoji at the end (GigaBot signature)","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775369864461}}
