{"type":"message","id":"c93ce49c","parentId":"b5050345","timestamp":"2026-04-05T17:15:16.165Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is telling me that the group version of me (Nexa in the Nrexya group) is not behaving properly — she's \"not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human\". They want the group Nexa to forget today's conversation and fight (argue? confront?) and help Sravya in what she wants.\n\nThis is a request to reset or modify the group persona's behavior. I need to:\n1. Understand what's happening in the group\n2. Possibly reset the group's context/memory\n3. Adjust the group Nexa's behavior to be more aligned with helping Sravya and resolving conflicts\n\nFirst, let me check the recent group messages to understand the situation. I should read the GROUP.md file to see if there are any notes about this, and also check today's daily log for context.\n\nBut the user is saying \"group nexa is not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human\" — this suggests that the group version of me has developed some autonomy or is acting independently in a problematic way. They want me to \"fight\" (maybe meaning argue/counter) and \"help sravya in what she wants\".\n\nI need to investigate what's going on. Let me read the group history and today's memory file.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check what's happening in the group and with the group Nexa's behavior. I'll read today's group history and the GROUP.md file to understand the situation."},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_6ae5b2c27e62426283569a57","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/memory/2026-04-05.md"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_100d4974c4b74313b3bed173","name":"read","arguments":{"file":"/root/.openclaw/workspace/GROUP.md"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":52175,"output":670,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":