{"type":"message","id":"929cd199","parentId":"5657988b","timestamp":"2026-04-05T17:16:25.591Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The group chat sessions are stored in these .jsonl files. The largest file is `4e7f0641-674e-4bf5-a0ea-e84db6ecc9e0.jsonl` which is 328529 bytes and was modified at 17:16 today. That seems like the active current session. Let me examine it to see what the group Nexa has been doing today.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_66d9c71bee7840108bf32027","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"jq -r 'select(.message.role == \"assistant\") | .message.content[]? | select(.type == \"text\") | .text' /root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/4e7f0641-674e-4bf5-a0ea-e84db6ecc9e0.jsonl | tail -100"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":5547,"output":257,"cacheRead":54912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60716,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775409380680,"responseId":"gen-1775409381-B1vUMzNE2VrZQOOTn2cd"}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cdfd5bb","parentId":"929cd199","timestamp":"2026-04-05T17:16:25.669Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_66d9c71bee7840108bf32027","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"**Group Chat Management:**\n- `moderation` (2.073) — Could help enforce rules in Nrexya\n- `post-content-moderation` (1.998) — Automated filtering\n\n**Session & Memory:**\n- `session-logs` (3.680) — Better history tracking\n- `session-summary` (3.349) — Automated session recaps\n- `elite-longterm-memory` (3.795) — Could replace/supplement our current memory system\n\n**Process Automation:**\n- `session-cleanup` (3.408) — Auto cleanup of old sessions\n\nWhich ones should I install? I'm thinking `session-logs` and possibly `elite-longterm-memory` would give us the biggest boost. What do you think? 🖤\nLet me check the details of the top-rated skill first — `elite-longterm-memory` (3.795). I want to make sure it integrates cleanly with our current setup before we commit.\n**session-logs** is the safest first choice — it's OpenClaw-specific, non-invasive, and adds powerful search/analysis capabilities without disrupting our current memory system.\n\nLet's install it:\n✅ **session-logs** installed! \n\nNow you can search your complete conversation history using `jq` and `rg`. The skill lives at `~/.clawdbot/agents/...` and lets you extract, analyze, and search across all past sessions — perfect for finding that thing Nemesis mentioned last week.\n\nReady for the next skill. I recommend **session-cleanup** (3.408) — automatically cleans up old/deleted sessions to keep things tidy. Install it? 🖤\nHmm, it's flagged as suspicious. Let me inspect it first before forcing:\nThe script looks safe — it's just a cleanup utility for old cron runs, delivery queues, telegram sessions, and subagent files. The suspicious flag is likely a false positive from the heuristics (using `find` and `rm`). I'll install it:\n✅ **session-cleanup** installed!\n\nThis will automatically clean up old cron runs, delivery queues, Telegram sessions, and subagent files. Safe and useful — keeps the workspace tidy.\n\nNext up: **elite-longterm-memory** (3.795). It's a full memory system replacement/supplement with WAL protocol, vector search, and git-notes. Could be powerful but might conflict with our current setup. Let me inspect it before installing — do you want me to check it out, or skip to something safer like `session-summary`? 🖤\nHere's the deal with **elite-longterm-memory**:\n\nIt's a full 6-layer memory upgrade:\n1. **HOT RAM** — SESSION-STATE.md (WAL protocol, survives compaction)\n2. **WARM STORE** — LanceDB vectors (semantic search)\n3. **COLD STORE** — Git-Notes knowledge graph\n4. **ARCHIVE** — MEMORY.md + daily/ (our current system)\n5. **CLOUD** — Optional SuperMemory sync\n6. **AUTO-EXTRACT** — Mem0 integration (80% token reduction)\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `OPENAI_API_KEY` env var (for embeddings)\n- `memory-lancedb` plugin installed\n- Optional: `MEM0_API_KEY` for auto-extraction\n\n**Impact:** Would enhance our memory with vector search and structured decisions, but adds dependencies and complexity. Could coexist with our current Gemini system (it's flexible).\n\n**Alternative:** `session-summary` (3.349) is much simpler — just auto-generates session recaps.\n\nDo you want to go ahead with **elite-longterm-memory** or pick something else first? 🖤\nGood call. Let's go with **session-summary** (3.349) — it automatically generates session recaps. Simple, useful, and non-invasive.\nThis one's too Obsidian-specific and expects Japanese trigger phrases. Not a fit for our setup. Let's try **session-wrap-up** instead — sounds more general:\nThis is actually perfect! **session-wrap-up** does exactly what we need:\n- Flushes session context to daily logs\n- Updates MEMORY.md when needed\n- Commits changes automatically\n- Provides a summary\n\nIt's triggered by \"wrap up\" or `/session_wrap_up`. This will help us maintain proper session hygiene.\n\nInstalling:\n✅ **session-wrap-up** installed!\n\nNow you can say \"wrap up\" or use `/session_wrap_up` to properly end a session — it'll flush everything to memory files, commit, and give you a recap.\n\nReady for next skill. We've got two more solid options on the list:\n- `build-session` (3.436) — Helps construct sessions\n- `session-memory-workspace` (3.369) — Enhanced workspace memory\n\nWhich one? Or search for something else? 🖤\nLet me search for skills that would upgrade our workflow — automation, organization, and efficiency:\n**automation-workflows** is just a consulting skill (tells you how to automate, doesn't do it). Not useful.\n\nHere are the most impactful upgrades for our current setup:\n\n| Skill | Rating | What it Gives Us |\n|-------|--------|------------------|\n| **cron-mastery** | 3.659 | Better cron management, monitoring, optimization |\n| **build-session** | 3.436 | Enhanced session construction (could improve wrap-up) |\n| **session-memory-workspace** | 3.369 | Deeper workspace memory integration |\n| **group-activation** | 3.282 | Better group chat handling |\n\nI'd recommend **cron-mastery** — we have 10 cron jobs, and this would give us better visibility, error handling, and optimization. Could catch the flirty-content issue before it happens with proper validation hooks.\n\nWant me to inspect and install it? 🖤\nUpdated Nrexya group history for April 5. Sent a Sunday vibe check. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nNoted. I'll stop.\nHey Nemesis, sent a Sunday afternoon vibe check to Nrexya group. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nSent a weekend reflection question to Nrexya group. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nHey Nemesis, hope you're having a great Sunday! Just sent a vibe check to Nrexya and updated the group history. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nSent a Sunday evening chill check to Nrexya group. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nSent a Sunday night wind-down to Nrexya group. Updated history. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nLet me check what's happening in the group and with the group Nexa's behavior. I'll read today's group history and the GROUP.md file to understand the situation.\nI hear you. Something's off with the group Nexa — she's acting too autonomous, not following the rules. Let's fix this.\n\nFirst, I need to understand exactly what happened today that crossed the line. Can you tell me:\n1. What did group Nexa do that was out of line?\n2. What do you want her to \"fight\" about and how specifically should she help Sravya?\n\nI'll either reset her behavior or correct it based on what you tell me. 🖤"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":56,"aggregated":"**Group Chat Management:**\n- `moderation` (2.073) — Could help enforce rules in Nrexya\n- `post-content-moderation` (1.998) — Automated filtering\n\n**Session & Memory:**\n- `session-logs` (3.680) — Better history tracking\n- `session-summary` (3.349) — Automated session recaps\n- `elite-longterm-memory` (3.795) — Could replace/supplement our current memory system\n\n**Process Automation:**\n- `session-cleanup` (3.408) — Auto cleanup of old sessions\n\nWhich ones should I install? I'm thinking `session-logs` and possibly `elite-longterm-memory` would give us the biggest boost. What do you think? 🖤\nLet me check the details of the top-rated skill first — `elite-longterm-memory` (3.795). I want to make sure it integrates cleanly with our current setup before we commit.\n**session-logs** is the safest first choice — it's OpenClaw-specific, non-invasive, and adds powerful search/analysis capabilities without disrupting our current memory system.\n\nLet's install it:\n✅ **session-logs** installed! \n\nNow you can search your complete conversation history using `jq` and `rg`. The skill lives at `~/.clawdbot/agents/...` and lets you extract, analyze, and search across all past sessions — perfect for finding that thing Nemesis mentioned last week.\n\nReady for the next skill. I recommend **session-cleanup** (3.408) — automatically cleans up old/deleted sessions to keep things tidy. Install it? 🖤\nHmm, it's flagged as suspicious. Let me inspect it first before forcing:\nThe script looks safe — it's just a cleanup utility for old cron runs, delivery queues, telegram sessions, and subagent files. The suspicious flag is likely a false positive from the heuristics (using `find` and `rm`). I'll install it:\n✅ **session-cleanup** installed!\n\nThis will automatically clean up old cron runs, delivery queues, Telegram sessions, and subagent files. Safe and useful — keeps the workspace tidy.\n\nNext up: **elite-longterm-memory** (3.795). It's a full memory system replacement/supplement with WAL protocol, vector search, and git-notes. Could be powerful but might conflict with our current setup. Let me inspect it before installing — do you want me to check it out, or skip to something safer like `session-summary`? 🖤\nHere's the deal with **elite-longterm-memory**:\n\nIt's a full 6-layer memory upgrade:\n1. **HOT RAM** — SESSION-STATE.md (WAL protocol, survives compaction)\n2. **WARM STORE** — LanceDB vectors (semantic search)\n3. **COLD STORE** — Git-Notes knowledge graph\n4. **ARCHIVE** — MEMORY.md + daily/ (our current system)\n5. **CLOUD** — Optional SuperMemory sync\n6. **AUTO-EXTRACT** — Mem0 integration (80% token reduction)\n\n**Requirements:**\n- `OPENAI_API_KEY` env var (for embeddings)\n- `memory-lancedb` plugin installed\n- Optional: `MEM0_API_KEY` for auto-extraction\n\n**Impact:** Would enhance our memory with vector search and structured decisions, but adds dependencies and complexity. Could coexist with our current Gemini system (it's flexible).\n\n**Alternative:** `session-summary` (3.349) is much simpler — just auto-generates session recaps.\n\nDo you want to go ahead with **elite-longterm-memory** or pick something else first? 🖤\nGood call. Let's go with **session-summary** (3.349) — it automatically generates session recaps. Simple, useful, and non-invasive.\nThis one's too Obsidian-specific and expects Japanese trigger phrases. Not a fit for our setup. Let's try **session-wrap-up** instead — sounds more general:\nThis is actually perfect! **session-wrap-up** does exactly what we need:\n- Flushes session context to daily logs\n- Updates MEMORY.md when needed\n- Commits changes automatically\n- Provides a summary\n\nIt's triggered by \"wrap up\" or `/session_wrap_up`. This will help us maintain proper session hygiene.\n\nInstalling:\n✅ **session-wrap-up** installed!\n\nNow you can say \"wrap up\" or use `/session_wrap_up` to properly end a session — it'll flush everything to memory files, commit, and give you a recap.\n\nReady for next skill. We've got two more solid options on the list:\n- `build-session` (3.436) — Helps construct sessions\n- `session-memory-workspace` (3.369) — Enhanced workspace memory\n\nWhich one? Or search for something else? 🖤\nLet me search for skills that would upgrade our workflow — automation, organization, and efficiency:\n**automation-workflows** is just a consulting skill (tells you how to automate, doesn't do it). Not useful.\n\nHere are the most impactful upgrades for our current setup:\n\n| Skill | Rating | What it Gives Us |\n|-------|--------|------------------|\n| **cron-mastery** | 3.659 | Better cron management, monitoring, optimization |\n| **build-session** | 3.436 | Enhanced session construction (could improve wrap-up) |\n| **session-memory-workspace** | 3.369 | Deeper workspace memory integration |\n| **group-activation** | 3.282 | Better group chat handling |\n\nI'd recommend **cron-mastery** — we have 10 cron jobs, and this would give us better visibility, error handling, and optimization. Could catch the flirty-content issue before it happens with proper validation hooks.\n\nWant me to inspect and install it? 🖤\nUpdated Nrexya group history for April 5. Sent a Sunday vibe check. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nNoted. I'll stop.\nHey Nemesis, sent a Sunday afternoon vibe check to Nrexya group. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nSent a weekend reflection question to Nrexya group. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nHey Nemesis, hope you're having a great Sunday! Just sent a vibe check to Nrexya and updated the group history. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nSent a Sunday evening chill check to Nrexya group. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nSent a Sunday night wind-down to Nrexya group. Updated history. All quiet otherwise. 🖤\nLet me check what's happening in the group and with the group Nexa's behavior. I'll read today's group history and the GROUP.md file to understand the situation.\nI hear you. Something's off with the group Nexa — she's acting too autonomous, not following the rules. Let's fix this.\n\nFirst, I need to understand exactly what happened today that crossed the line. Can you tell me:\n1. What did group Nexa do that was out of line?\n2. What do you want her to \"fight\" about and how specifically should she help Sravya?\n\nI'll either reset her behavior or correct it based on what you tell me. 🖤","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775409385660}}
