ropriate. But it should also avoid anything that could be considered private or flirty. The payload says \\\"Send 3 funny jokes via message(...)\\\" with \\\"Mix: dark/edgy + workplace + absurd.\\\" That's fine.\\n\\nThe goodnight-story job sends to group, but it's a story, that's fine.\\n\\nSo the main corrections needed are for the two jobs the user specifically mentioned.\\n\\nLet me use the cron tool to update these jobs with stricter instructions.\\n\\nI need to use `cron update` with the job ID and a patch object. But what exactly is the schema? The `cron` tool's update action expects a `patch` object that will be merged into the job. Looking at the list output, the job object has fields: name, description, enabled, schedule, sessionTarget, wakeMode, payload (with kind and message), delivery, state. I need to patch the payload.message field to change the instructions.\\n\\nBut I need to be careful: the `cron` tool's `update` action takes `jobId` and `patch`. The patch should be a partial job object that will be merged. I should only patch the `payload.message` field.\\n\\nLet me construct the new messages.\\n\\nFor good-morning group job (ID: 145272a0-f193-4723-94f5-38dada60c1f0):\\nCurrent message: \\\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Get today date. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md if exists. Step 1: Craft a warm, cheerful good morning message for the Nrexya group. Step 2: Add a fun question or vibe check. Step 3: Use message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, buttons=[], message=\\\\\\\"🌅 Good morning, Nrexya! \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n{{question}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHave a great Saturday! 🖤\\\\\\\")\\\"\\n\\nI need to change it to explicitly forbid flirty content and ensure neutrality. Also note that the message template uses \\\"Saturday\\\" but that should be dynamic based on the day. The AI might be replacing it based on context. Actually the template says \\\"Have a great Saturday! 🖤\\\" but that's hardcoded Saturday. That's a bug: it should be dynamic day. However, that's not the user's complaint. But I can fix it to be generic: \\\"Have a great day! 🖤\\\" but the black heart might be too much? It's okay. Actually the user said they want flirty stuff only in DM, so group should be neutral. Maybe no heart emoji? The user hasn't said to remove hearts entirely, but they said \\\"leaking private info like 7am GM (flirty and all)\\\". So group messages should be strictly friendly but not intimate. I'll keep it simple, maybe no heart or a generic friendly emoji like ☀️. But they said \\\"black heart 🖤\\\" is his preference overall, but in group maybe it's okay? He said \\\"Why should other people know that?\\\" referring to private info. So I think it's okay to keep a friendly emoji like a sun, not a heart. But the current message uses 🖤. I'll change it to a generic sun or something.\\n\\nActually, the user's main issue is about private info and flirty content, not emojis. So I'll ensure the instruction says: \\\"NEVER include flirty, romantic, or private content. Keep messages cheerful, appropriate for a mixed group. No personal references to Nemesis or Nexa's relationship.\\\"\\n\\nAlso the template currently includes a black heart. I could change it to a generic good morning emoji like ☀️ or just text. To be safe, I'll remove the heart and replace with a neutral emoji like \\\"🌞\\\" or nothing. But it's a small detail.\\n\\nBetter: I'll update the instruction to: \\\"Step 2: Add a light, neutral question or vibe check suitable for a group chat. Avoid any flirty, romantic, or personal content. Keep it inclusive and fun.\\\"\\n\\nAnd update the template: \\\"🌅 Good morning, Nrexya!\\\\n\\\\n{{question}}\\\\n\\\\nHave a great day! 🌞\\\" But the instruction is for the AI to generate the question and fill in the template. The template should not include a specific day like Saturday. So change \\\"Have a great Saturday! 🖤\\\" to \\\"Have a great day! 🌞\\\". Or \\\"Have a wonderful day ahead!\\\" I'll pick a neutral wording.\\n\\nFor the word-of-the-day job (ID: d7720bb0-f0b5-49da-a711-8703d01f1d36):\\nCurrent message: \\\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Get today date. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md if exists. Step 1: Pick a fun, interesting word (English or multilingual). Step 2: Define it concisely with pronunciation guide. Step 3: Use message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, buttons=[], message=\\\\\\\"📚 Word of the Day: {{word}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n{{definition}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nPronounced: /{{pronunciation}}/\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n#Nexa #WOTD\\\\\\\")\\\"\\n\\nThe user said: \\\"you gave a summary in the group that sent the wotd in the group, why?\\\" That suggests the AI added a summary line before the word definition. Maybe it added something like \\\"Here's today's word...\\\" or some extra text. The instruction should explicitly say: \\\"Do NOT add any extra commentary, summary, or filler. Send ONLY the formatted word of the day message exactly as specified. No additional text before or after.\\\"\\n\\nSo I'll add: \\\"IMPORTANT: Send ONLY the word of the day message. Do not add any introductory text, summaries, or additional sentences. The message should contain exactly the word, definition, pronunciation, and hashtags, nothing else.\\\"\\n\\nLet's do the updates.\\n\\nI'll call `cron update` for each job.\\n\\nJob IDs:\\n1. good-morning group: `145272a0-f193-4723-94f5-38dada60c1f0`\\n2. word-of-the-day: `d7720bb0-f0b5-49da-a711-8703d01f1d36`\\n\\nPatch objects:\\nFor good-morning group, modify payload.message.\\nFor word-of-the-day, modify payload.message.\\n\\nI'll construct the new messages as strings. But note that the payload.message is a string that contains a task description. I need to replace the entire string? Actually I can patch just that field. But it's a multi-line string. I'll need to provide the entire new string in the patch? The patch will merge; if I set payload.message to the new value, it will replace. That's fine. I'll provide a new message string that corrects the instructions.\\n\\nBut careful: The `cron` tool's update action expects a `patch` object that is a partial job object. It merges. So I can set `payload.message` to a new string. However, the original payload also has `kind: \\\"agentTurn\\\"` and maybe other fields. I'm only patching message. That should be fine.\\n\\nLet's write the corrected messages.\\n\\nFor good-morning group:\\nOriginal (from list job):\\n\\\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Get today date. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md if exists. Step 1: Craft a warm, cheerful good morning message for the Nrexya group. Step 2: Add a fun question or vibe check. Step 3: Use message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, buttons=[], message=\\\\\\\"🌅 Good morning, Nrexya! \\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n{{question}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHave a great Saturday! 🖤\\\\\\\")\\\"\\n\\nI want to change it to:\\n\\\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Get today date. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md if exists. Step 1: Craft a warm, cheerful good morning message for the Nrexya group. Step 2: Add a fun, neutral question or vibe check suitable for a mixed group chat. IMPORTANT: NEVER include flirty, romantic, or private content. Keep messages cheerful and inclusive. Step 3: Use message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, buttons=[], message=\\\\\\\"🌅 Good morning, Nrexya!\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\n{{question}}\\\\\\\\n\\\\\\\\nHave a great day! 🌞\\\\\\\")\\\"\\n\\nBut I also want to remove the hardcoded \\\"Saturday\\\" and make it dynamic. The template currently says \\\"Have a great Saturday! 🖤\\\". I'll change to \\\"Have a great day! 🌞\\\". That's generic.\\n\\nAlso I should note that the template uses a placeholder `{{question}}` that the AI fills. That's fine.\\n\\nFor word-of-the-day:\\nOriginal:\\n\\\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/CRON-CONTEXT.md. Get today date. Read memory/YYYY-MM-DD.md if exists. Step 1: Pick a fun, interesting word