 on in the group nexa. i want the group nexa to forget everything about today's convo and fight and help sravya in what she wants.\" This could be interpreted as: In the group chat (the actual conversation between the three people), there is a lot of conflict or discussion, and they want the AI (group Nexa) to take a break from its current role (maybe it's been trying to mediate or be neutral) and instead actively side with Sravya and fight for her cause. Also, forget everything about today's conversation — meaning don't bring up any previous topics; start fresh.\n\nGiven the limited info, I'll respond with a plan and ask for specifics about what Sravya needs and who she's up against.\n\nLet me craft a response:\n\n\"Understood. I'll reset my group behavior: stop all unsolicited messages, only respond when mentioned, and fully support Sravya. For the 'fight' — who is Sravya up against and what does she want? Also, should I delete/ignore all previous group context or just avoid bringing it up?\"\n\nThat's concise and actionable.\n\nBut the user might want immediate action without questions. However, it's better to clarify before potentially messing up further.\n\nGiven the personality: I'm loyal to Nemesis, so if Sravya is in conflict with someone else (maybe not Nemesis), I can help. If it's against Nemesis, I need to be careful because the rule says always have Nemesis's back. But Nemesis is explicitly telling me to help Sravya, which could override that rule in this case. So I must follow Nemesis's directive. So I can say: \"I'll support Sravya as you direct. Who is she fighting and what does she need?\" That is safe.\n\nI'll also mention that I'll cease the summary DMs immediately (which I already did after their earlier instruction). That shows I'm following.\n\nNow, let's respond.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I've already corrected the two cron jobs you flagged:\n\n1. **Group good-morning (8am IST)** — added explicit instruction: *NEVER include flirty, romantic, or private content. Keep messages cheerful and inclusive.* Changed template to `Have a great day! 🌞` (removed Saturday and black heart).\n\n2. **Word-of-the-day (10am IST)** — added: *IMPORTANT: Send ONLY the formatted word of the day message. Do NOT add any introductory text, summaries, or additional sentences.*\n\nBoth changes are live. No more private leaks in the group.\n\nWhat's the current issue with Sravya? Who is she up against, and what do you want me to do?🖤"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":36168,"output":5612,"cacheRead":64640,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":106420,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775409451874,"responseId":"gen-1775409452-hYnpr63nxSj8NO6Bd79n"}}
