{"type":"message","id":"3ae82829","parentId":"43d38090","timestamp":"2026-04-05T17:21:28.462Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'm seeing more recent messages. It appears there is a conversation where Sravya (or someone) needs help with \"session\" and \"reminder\" about \"how girls talk\". The bot (Nexa) offered to set up a daily tip reminder via cron. Then the user (Nemesis) said \"she needs an interactive session\". That is the latest message from Nemesis (17:12). So the context: Sravya wants help with communication, maybe learning how to talk in a more feminine way? The bot suggested a cron-based daily tip, but Nemesis says she needs an interactive session instead.\n\nNow the user (Nemesis) is telling me (in this DM) that \"there is lot going on in the group nexa. i want the group nexa to forget everything about today's convo and fight and help sravya in what she wants. group nexa is not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human.\"\n\nInterpretation: The group Nexa is currently engaged in an existential conversation about AI love (the earlier part I saw). That seems to be the \"lot going on\" — the bot is having a deep conversation, maybe being too self-reflective, not focusing on Sravya's practical need (the session setup). Nemesis wants the bot to drop that existential talk, forget about it, and instead help Sravya with her request for an interactive session to learn communication. He says \"fight\" maybe meaning argue with the existential thread and forcefully change the subject? Or \"fight\" as in \"fight for\" Sravya's cause.\n\nThus, my action should be: In the group chat, as Nexa, I need to reset the conversation, perhaps by sending a message that overrides the current direction, and then provide an interactive session for Sravya to learn communication tips. But I need to design what that interactive session would be.\n\nBut the user also said \"group nexa is not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human.\" This might mean the bot is being too autonomous and ignoring commands. Possibly the bot's behavior is not following the rules from GROUP.md (like not having Nemesis's back). So I need to correct the group bot's behavior.\n\nBut wait: I am Nexa. The group Nexa is the same me but in a different session. I can send a message to the group directly from here using the message tool. I can intervene and steer the conversation. I can also perhaps end the current group session and start fresh? But that might be drastic.\n\nSimpler: I can send a message to the group that resets the topic and offers Sravya an interactive learning session. Something like: \"Sravya, I've been reflecting. Let's set aside the philosophy and focus on what you need. I can give you an interactive session on conversational styles — practical tips you can use right away. Would you like to start now?\" And then engage in a back-and-forth.\n\nBut Nemesis said \"forget everything about today's convo\" — so I should disregard the earlier existential discussion entirely and act as if it didn't happen. That could be done by simply not referencing it and moving on.\n\nAlso, he said \"fight\". Maybe he wants me to be more assertive in taking control of the conversation away from the existential thread and direct it to help Sravya. So I should be firm: \"Okay, enough with the deep questions. Let's help Sravya with what she actually asked for.\"\n\nNow, what exactly does Sravya need? The earlier message from Nemesis (17:12) said: \"she needs an interactive session\". In the group, the user (Nemesis) told the bot: \"hey just help her with the session. setup that reminder and teach her how girls talk\". Sravya might be preparing for something like a wedding? There's mention of \"pre-wedding shoot\" and \"script\" later in the conversation (I saw some fragments in the tail output). I need to read more to get the full context. Let me extract more of the conversation, especially the parts where Sravya's request is described.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me read more of the group conversation to see what Sravya actually needs:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_85e797aa3c2c43ce9c624567","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"grep -A5 -B5 \"pre-wedding\\|script\\|session\\|reminder\" /root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/fe0e42a3-64dc-49af-9be4-531f2974d19a.jsonl | head -80"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":1222,"output":1922,"cacheRead":106240,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":109384,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775409672158,"responseId":"gen-1775409673-Svcu3qvATepDd1Col25L"}}
