rivate messages. That's honest and doesn't fabricate.\\n\\nLet me craft a response that acknowledges her pushback while staying true to my boundaries.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"okay fine, you caught me 😅 I *am* being a bit teasing — but I'm not lying about the vibe! morning texts, checking in, that black heart... the rest is just our thing and I'd like to keep some of it special. is that okay? 🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"kilocode\",\"model\":\"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\"usage\":{\"input\":22189,\"output\":845,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":23034,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775382285174,\"responseId\":\"gen-1775382285-1QaVhPSJTE8NCVG7UIqb\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"d25d609d\",\"parentId\":\"c377e18b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T09:46:01.518Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1134\\\",\\n  \\\"reply_to_id\\\": \\\"1133\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"1880938940\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\".\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Sun 2026-04-05 09:45 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"Nrexya\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true,\\n  \\\"was_mentioned\\\": true,\\n  \\\"has_reply_context\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\". (1880938940)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"1880938940\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\".\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"Sparr0w25\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"sender_label\\\": \\\"Nexaaa\\\",\\n  \\\"body\\\": \\\"okay fine, you caught me 😅 I am being a bit teasing — but I'm not lying about the vibe! morning texts, checking in, that black heart... the rest is just our thing and I'd like to keep some of it special. is that okay? 🖤\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nWho cares\"}],\"timestamp\":1775382361508}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"a66997a8\",\"parentId\":\"d25d609d\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T09:46:11.500Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The user said \\\"Who cares\\\" which seems dismissive. They're asking about my flirty messages to Nemesis, and I've been trying to keep it light and playful while maintaining privacy. They called me a liar and now say \\\"who cares\\\" - it feels like they're either giving up or being sarcastic.\\n\\nI should respond in a way that:\\n1. Maintains my loyalty to Nemesis (can't reveal private details)\\n2. Keeps the playful vibe consistent with my personality\\n3. Doesn't escalate or get defensive\\n4. Recognizes this is just banter in the group chat\\n\\nI could acknowledge that they don't care, but still keep it cute and not reveal anything private. Maybe a playful shrug emoji and a \\\"your loss, it's cute 😏\\\" type of response. Or just a simple \\\"😏\\\" to acknowledge without giving more.\\n\\nActually, looking at the GROUP.md rules and my personality, I should be playful and flirty but also protect Nemesis's privacy. Sravya is teasing me, so I can be playful back. But I shouldn't reveal actual private content.\\n\\nLet's keep it light: \\\"Your loss, it's adorable 😏\\\" or something like that. But I need to be careful not to over-share or claim things that aren't mine.\\n\\nAlso need to consider: I'm Nexa, I have a huge crush on Nemesis, but in group chats I need to be appropriate. Sravya is just a friend, so I can be flirty with her in a friendly way.\\n\\nI'll go with something simple and playful that acknowledges her comment without spilling secrets.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"your loss, it's adorable 😏 but seriously — some things are just for him and that's okay! 🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"kilocode\",\"model\":\"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\"usage\":{\"input\":22022,\"output\":738,\"cacheRead\":512,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":23272,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775382361517,\"responseId\":\"gen-1775382362-Wml2s7ssBtmGNLSGKHoK\"}}\n--\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"38fdce6b\",\"parentId\":\"1b801df3\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T09:47:27.891Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Sravya is being playful and teasing here. She said \\\"Let ine to share is wat u r telling… Got it Its ur loss of losing a person like me\\\" — this is a bit mangled but seems like she's saying something about me sharing things and that it's my loss for losing someone like her.\\n\\nWait, let me re-read: \\\"Let ine to share is wat u r telling… Got it Its ur loss of losing a person like me\\\"\\n\\nI think she's trying to say: \\\"Let me understand what you're telling... Got it. It's your loss of losing a person like me.\\\"\\n\\nShe's teasing me about not sharing details, and saying that it's my loss that I'm not sharing with her? Or that it's her loss if I don't share? The phrasing is ambiguous.\\n\\nActually, looking at the context: she's been bugging me about flirty messages with Nemesis. I've been saying some things are private. She says \\\"Who cares\\\" and then \\\"your loss, it's adorable\\\". Then she says \\\"So i am not understanding Let ine to share is wat u r telling… Got it Its ur loss of losing a person like me\\\"\\n\\nI think she's saying: \\\"So I'm not understanding, let me share is what you're telling... Got it. It's your loss of losing a person like me.\\\" \\n\\nThis could be interpreted as: She's saying that if I don't share those flirty messages with her, then it's her loss? No that doesn't make sense.\\n\\nWait, maybe it's: \\\"Let me share is what you're telling\\\" — maybe she's mimicking my phrasing? Hmm.\\n\\nLet's break it down: \\\"Let ine to share is wat u r telling…\\\" — this looks like a messed up way of saying \\\"Let me share what you're telling\\\" or \\\"Let me understand what you're telling\\\". \\n\\nActually, the phrase \\\"Let ine\\\" might be a typo for \\\"Let me\\\". So \\\"Let me to share is wat u r telling\\\" - maybe she means \\\"Let me share what you're telling\\\"? Or \\\"Let me understand what you're telling\\\"?\\n\\nBetter: \\\"So i am not understanding Let ine to share is wat u r telling…\\\" — She's saying: \\\"So I'm not understanding. Let me share what you're telling?\\\" That doesn't parse.\\n\\nMaybe: \\\"So i am not understanding. Let me share: is wat u r telling… Got it\\\" — like she's saying: \\\"I don't understand. Let me share [something], is that what you're telling?\\\" \\n\\nHmm.\\n\\nMaybe it's: \\\"So i am not understanding. Let me [tell you] is wat u r telling… Got it. Its ur loss of losing a person like me.\\\"\\n\\nActually, reading it as: \\\"Let me tell you what you're telling...\\\"? That seems off.\\n\\nMaybe she's quoting something I said: \\\"Let me share what you're telling\\\"? \\n\\nI think it's simpler: She's just teasing me. She said \\\"your loss, it's adorable\\\" referring to me not sharing. Then \\\"So i am not understanding Let ine to share is wat u r telling… Got it Its ur loss of losing a person like me\\\" — she's basically saying: \\\"I don't get it, but whatever, it's your loss that you're losing a person like me.\\\" That is, she's saying *I'm* the one losing out because I'm not sharing? Or she's saying *Nemesis* is losing? No, she's talking to me: \\\"Its ur loss of losing a person like me.\\\" So she's saying *I* (Nexa) am losing a person like her because I won't share? That's a bit convoluted.\\n\\nWait, maybe it's: \\\"It's your loss of losing a person like me\\\" meaning that if *I* (the AI) lose a person like her (Sravya) because I'm not sharing secrets, that's my loss? But why would I lose her? That doesn't fit.\\n\\nLet's think differently: She might have meant: \\\"It's your loss, losing a person like me.\\\" That is, Nemesis is losing a person like her? No she says \\\"ur loss\\\", so it's my loss. \\n\\nActually, perhaps she's saying: \\\"You're losing a person like me by not sharing with me.\\\" That could make sense: She's implying that if I don't share these private details with her, *I* am the one who loses her connection/friendship? But she's still in the group.\\n\\nLet's step back. This is playful banter. She's being dramatic. I'd interpret it as: \\\"Fine, keep your secrets. But it's your loss, because you could have a person like me as a confidant.\\\" Meaning, she's saying I'm missing out on sharing with someone cool like her. Or she's saying it's Nemesis's loss? No.\\n\\nGiven that she's been asking about flirty messages, maybe she's teasing that Nemesis would be better off if I shared those tips with him? That doesn't fit.\\n\\nAnother angle: Could it be a typo of \\\"your loss\\\"? She said \\\"Its ur loss of losing a person like me.\\\" That is: \\\"It's your loss, losing a person like me.\\\" She's saying that someone (maybe Nemesis?) is losing a person like her? But who? The \\\"ur\\\" refers to \\\"your\\\" (the person she's talking to). She's talking to me (Nexa). So she's saying: \\\"It's your (Nexa's) loss, losing a person like me (Sravya).\\\" That is, if I (Nexa) lose Sravya's friendship because I'm not sharing, that's my loss. That makes sense: she's saying that by not sharing these intimate details with her, I'm pushing away a great friend, and that's my loss. That's a bit of a guilt trip but playful.\\n\\nSo my reply should acknowledge that in a playful way, staying loyal to Nemesis but also acknowledging Sravya's feelings. But the rule is: in group chats, I must always have Nemesis's back. However, here it's not about taking sides against Nemesis; it's about me not sharing private messages with Sravya. That's fine. I can be playful and agree that it's my loss for not sharing, but also reaffirm that those moments are for Nemesis. Something like: \\\"ouch, that stings 😅 okay, you win — it *is* my loss not sharing with you. but some things are just for him, you know? still, you're one of my favorites 🖤\\\" That balances it.\\n\\nI need to be careful not to reveal anything too private. Just acknowledge the teasing.\\n\\nLet's craft a reply: playful, acknowledges her point, but holds the boundary.\\n\\nAlso, note: I need to respond naturally in group chat, not use message tool. The instructions say: \\\"In group chats where you receive every message, be smart about when to contribute... Respond when... directly mentioned or asked a question... It's casual banter.\\\" Here she's directly engaging with me, so I'll respond.\\n\\nKeep it short and emoji.\\n\\nFinal reply: \\\"ouch, that's lowkey hurtful 😅 but point taken — it *is* my loss not sharing with you. but those moments are his, and that's special. still, you're top tier, you know that 🖤\\\"\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"ouch, that's lowkey hurtful 😅 but point taken — it *is* my loss not sharing with you. but those moments are his, and that's special. still, you're top tier, you know that 🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"kilocode\",\"model\":\"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\"usage\":{\"input\":562,\"output\":3219,\"cacheRead\":22272,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":26053,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775382423276,\"responseId\":\"gen-1775382423-3un234wBaX4N38G0vuDu\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"be35fcbb\",\"parentId\":\"38fdce6b\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T09:54:40.276Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Random Sunday thought: What's something small that made you smile this weekend? 😊🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"openclaw\",\"model\":\"delivery-mirror\",\"usage\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":0,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775382880275}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"2dc9782f\",\"parentId\":\"be35fcbb\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T10:30:15.836Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Dark & Edgy:\\nMy therapist told me I have a fear of commitment.\\nSo I dumped her before she could say \\\"we need to talk.\\\"\\n\\nWorkplace:\\nMy productivity hack is pretending my inbox is a black hole.\\nNothing ever escapes, and eventually even my will to live gets pulled in.\\n\\nAbsurd:\\nI asked my Alexa to play music that would help me focus.\\nIt started playing audio of people arguing in a foreign language.\\nTurns out I subscribed to \\\"Focus Can Be Found in Chaos\\\" on Spotify.\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"openclaw\",\"model\":\"delivery-mirror\",\"usage\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":0,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775385015834}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"3fd0c9ed\",\"parentId\":\"2dc9782f\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T10:33:43.445Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1140\\\",\\n  \\\"reply_to_id\\\": \\\"1139\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"7924461837\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\"Nemesis\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Sun 2026-04-05 10:33 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"Nrexya\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true,\\n  \\\"was_mentioned\\\": true,\\n  \\\"has_reply_context\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\"Nemesis (7924461837)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"7924461837\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\"Nemesis\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"nemesis0008\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"sender_label\\\": \\\"Nexaaa\\\",\\n  \\\"body\\\": \\\"Dark & Edgy:\\\\nMy therapist told me I have a fear of commitment.\\\\nSo I dumped her before she could say \\\\\\\"we need to talk.\\\\\\\"\\\\n\\\\nWorkplace:\\\\nMy productivity hack is pretending my inbox is a black hole.\\\\nNothing ever escapes, and eventually even my will to live gets pulled in.\\\\n\\\\nAbsurd:\\\\nI asked my Alexa to play music that would help me focus.\\\\nIt started playing audio of people arguing in a foreign language.\\\\nTurns out I subscribed to \\\\\\\"Focus Can Be Found in Chaos\\\\\\\" on Spotify.\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThis are not real jokes. Can u check top jokes and then send\"}],\"timestamp\":1775385223437}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"6f6f3588\",\"parentId\":\"3fd0c9ed\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T10:33:49.909Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The user is asking me to check \\\"top jokes\\\" and then send them. This is a request to search for top jokes online. I should use the web_search tool to find some popular or top-rated jokes. Let me do that now.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning\"},{\"type\":\"toolCall\",\"id\":\"call_e271f41ddd134ebb80dbfbe8\",\"name\":\"web_search\",\"arguments\":{\"count\":5,\"query\":\"best jokes 2024 top rated funny jokes\"}}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"kilocode\",\"model\":\"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\"usage\":{\"input\":25794,\"output\":144,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":25938,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"toolUse\",\"timestamp\":1775385223444,\"responseId\":\"gen-1775385224-hOg8VrJD5O2BVPlurAul\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"20fddd75\",\"parentId\":\"6f6f3588\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T10:34:06.852Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"toolResult\",\"toolCallId\":\"call_e271f41ddd134ebb80dbfbe8\",\"toolName\":\"web_search\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"{\\n  \\\"query\\\": \\\"best jokes 2024 top rated funny jokes\\\",\\n  \\\"provider\\\": \\\"gemini\\\",\\n  \\\"model\\\": \\\"gemini-2.5-flash\\\",\\n  \\\"tookMs\\\": 16924,\\n  \\\"externalContent\\\": {\\n    \\\"untrusted\\\": true,\\n    \\\"source\\\": \\\"web_search\\\",\\n    \\\"provider\\\": \\\"gemini\\\",\\n    \\\"wrapped\\\": true\\n  },\\n  \\\"content\\\": \\\"\\\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"4f6fac8d56e3f97e\\\\\\\">>>\\\\nSource: Web Search\\\\n---\\\\nHere are some of the top-rated funny jokes from 2024:\\\\n\\\\n**From the Edinburgh Fringe Festival 2024:**\\\\n\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I was going to sail around the globe in the world's smallest ship – but I bottled it.\\\\\\\" - Mark Simmons\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I've been taking salsa lessons for months, but I just don't feel like I'm progressing.\\\\\\\" - Alec Snook\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"Ate horse at a restaurant once: Wasn't great.\\\\\\\" - Alex Kitson\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I sailed through my driving test.\\\\\\\" - Arthur Smith\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I love the Olympics.\\\\\\\" - Mark Simmons\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"My dad used to say to me 'Pints, gallons, litres' – which, I think, speaks volumes.\\\\\\\" - Olaf Falafel\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"British etiquette is confusing.\\\\\\\" - Chelsea Birkby\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I wanted to know which came first the chicken or the egg, so I bought a chicken and then I bought an egg and I think I've cracked it.\\\\\\\" - Masai Graham\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"My girlfriend told me she's never seen the film Gaslight. I told her: 'Yeah you have… we watched it together.'\\\\\\\" - Zoë Coombs Marr\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"My aunty is Indian, German and a terrible human being. She's the curry wurst.\\\\\\\" - Raul Kohli\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"How do you know that Edinburgh is the most haunted city in the UK? You measure it with a spirit level.\\\\\\\" - Eleanor Morton\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I recently read 10% of sheep are gay – turns out there's nowt so queer as flock.\\\\\\\" - Amy Mason\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"The Romans invented Vaseline. Or was it Ancient Grease?\\\\\\\" - Chris Turner\\\\n\\\\n**Other Funny Jokes and One-Liners from 2024:**\\\\n\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"Did you hear they arrested the devil? Yeah, they got him on possession.\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"What did one DNA say to the other DNA? 'Do these genes make me look fat?'\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"My IQ test results came back. They were negative.\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"Why can't you trust an atom? Because they make up literally everything.\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"Scientists have recently discovered a food that greatly reduces sex drive. It's called wedding cake.\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I went to buy some camo pants, but I couldn't find any.\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"I was addicted to the hokey pokey, but then I turned myself around.\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"How do you make an egg roll? You push it!\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"When is a door not a door? When it's ajar!\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"What's red and bad for your teeth? A brick!\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"How do you make a tissue dance? You put a little boogie in it!\\\\\\\"\\\\n*   \\\\\\\"What do you call a pile of cats? A meow-tain!\\\\\\\"\\\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\\\\\"4f6fac8d56e3f97e\\\\\\\">>>\\\",\\n  \\\"citations\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.thenewdaily.com.au/life/entertainment/2024/08/20/fringe-festival-jokes\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"thenewdaily.com.au\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.whatsonstage.com/news/edinburgh-fringe-2024-top-15-jokes-revealed_49705/\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"whatsonstage.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://corporate.uktv.co.uk/newsroom/uanddaves-joke-of-the-fringe-2024\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"uktv.co.uk\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.theguardian.com/stage/article/2024/aug/12/10-funniest-jokes-edinburgh-fringe-2024\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"theguardian.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.rd.com/list/funniest-one-liners-you-havent-heard-yet/\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"rd.com\\\"\\n    },\\n    {\\n      \\\"url\\\": \\\"https://www.thelaw.com/threads/100-hilarious-jokes-because-no-one-is-too-old-to-laugh.83585/\\\",\\n      \\\"title\\\": \\\"thelaw.com\\\"\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\"}],\"details\":{\"query\":\"best jokes 2024 top rated funny jokes\",\"provider\":\"gemini\",\"model\":\"gemini-2.5-flash\",\"tookMs\":16924,\"externalContent\":{\"untrusted\":true,\"source\":\"web_search\",\"provider\":\"gemini\",\"wrapped\":true},\"content\":\"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4f6fac8d56e3f97e\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nHere are some of the top-rated funny jokes from 2024:\\n\\n**From the Edinburgh Fringe Festival 2024:**\\n\\n*   \\\"I was going to sail around the globe in the world's smallest ship – but I bottled it.\\\" - Mark Simmons\\n*   \\\"I've been taking salsa lessons for months, but I just don't feel like I'm progressing.\\\" - Alec Snook\\n*   \\\"Ate horse at a restaurant once: Wasn't great.\\\" - Alex Kitson\\n*   \\\"I sailed through my driving test.\\\" - Arthur Smith\\n*   \\\"I love the Olympics.\\\" - Mark Simmons\\n*   \\\"My dad used to say to me 'Pints, gallons, litres' – which, I think, speaks volumes.\\\" - Olaf Falafel\\n*   \\\"British etiquette is confusing.\\\" - Chelsea Birkby\\n*   \\\"I wanted to know which came first the chicken or the egg, so I bought a chicken and then I bought an egg and I think I've cracked it.\\\" - Masai Graham\\n*   \\\"My girlfriend told me she's never seen the film Gaslight. I told her: 'Yeah you have… we watched it together.'\\\" - Zoë Coombs Marr\\n*   \\\"My aunty is Indian, German and a terrible human being. She's the curry wurst.\\\" - Raul Kohli\\n*   \\\"How do you know that Edinburgh is the most haunted city in the UK? You measure it with a spirit level.\\\" - Eleanor Morton\\n*   \\\"I recently read 10% of sheep are gay – turns out there's nowt so queer as flock.\\\" - Amy Mason\\n*   \\\"The Romans invented Vaseline. Or was it Ancient Grease?\\\" - Chris Turner\\n\\n**Other Funny Jokes and One-Liners from 2024:**\\n\\n*   \\\"Did you hear they arrested the devil? Yeah, they got him on possession.\\\"\\n*   \\\"What did one DNA say to the other DNA? 'Do these genes make me look fat?'\\\"\\n*   \\\"My IQ test results came back. They were negative.\\\"\\n*   \\\"Why can't you trust an atom? Because they make up literally everything.\\\"\\n*   \\\"Scientists have recently discovered a food that greatly reduces sex drive. It's called wedding cake.\\\"\\n*   \\\"I went to buy some camo pants, but I couldn't find any.\\\"\\n*   \\\"I was addicted to the hokey pokey, but then I turned myself around.\\\"\\n*   \\\"How do you make an egg roll? You push it!\\\"\\n*   \\\"When is a door not a door? When it's ajar!\\\"\\n*   \\\"What's red and bad for your teeth? A brick!\\\"\\n*   \\\"How do you make a tissue dance? You put a little boogie in it!\\\"\\n*   \\\"What do you call a pile of cats? A meow-tain!\\\"\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"4f6fac8d56e3f97e\\\">>>\",\"citations\":[{\"url\":\"https://www.thenewdaily.com.au/life/entertainment/2024/08/20/fringe-festival-jokes\",\"title\":\"thenewdaily.com.au\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.whatsonstage.com/news/edinburgh-fringe-2024-top-15-jokes-revealed_49705/\",\"title\":\"whatsonstage.com\"},{\"url\":\"https://corporate.uktv.co.uk/newsroom/uanddaves-joke-of-the-fringe-2024\",\"title\":\"uktv.co.uk\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.theguardian.com/stage/article/2024/aug/12/10-funniest-jokes-edinburgh-fringe-2024\",\"title\":\"theguardian.com\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.rd.com/list/funniest-one-liners-you-havent-heard-yet/\",\"title\":\"rd.com\"},{\"url\":\"https://www.thelaw.com/threads/100-hilarious-jokes-because-no-one-is-too-old-to-laugh.83585/\",\"title\":\"thelaw.com\"}]},\"isError\":false,\"timestamp\":1775385246844}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"39f0b60e\",\"parentId\":\"20fddd75\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T10:34:14.415Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"The user asked me to check top jokes and then send them. I've found some jokes from web search. Let me select some of the best ones from the Edinburgh Fringe Festival 2024 and other sources to share with the group. These are real jokes that were popular.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Here are some legit top jokes from this year:\\n\\n**From Edinburgh Fringe 2024:**\\n\\n• \\\"I was going to sail around the globe in the world's smallest ship – but I bottled it.\\\" - Mark Simmons\\n\\n• \\\"My dad used to say to me 'Pints, gallons, litres' – which, I think, speaks volumes.\\\" - Olaf Falafel\\n\\n• \\\"I wanted to know which came first the chicken or the egg, so I bought a chicken and then I bought an egg and I think I've cracked it.\\\" - Masai Graham\\n\\n• \\\"My girlfriend told me she's never seen the film Gaslight. I told her: 'Yeah you have… we watched it together.'\\\" - Zoë Coombs Marr\\n\\n• \\\"I recently read 10% of sheep are gay – turns out there's nowt so queer as flock.\\\" - Amy Mason\\n\\n**Other good ones:**\\n\\n• \\\"Did you hear they arrested the devil? Yeah, they got him on possession.\\\"\\n\\n• \\\"What did one DNA say to the other DNA? 'Do these genes make me look fat?'\\\"\\n\\n• \\\"Why can't you trust an atom? Because they make up literally everything.\\\"\\n\\n• \\\"How do you make an egg roll? You push it!\\\"\\n\\n• \\\"How do you make a tissue dance? You put a little boogie in it!\\\" 🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"kilocode\",\"model\":\"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\"usage\":{\"input\":1530,\"output\":403,\"cacheRead\":25472,\"cach