y movie\\\". This is from the conversation with Sravya. I need to find out what specific movies she watched.\\n\\nLooking at the conversation, Sravya said she watched two movies today: one suspense and one comedy. She hasn't specified the titles. I can't magically know which movies she watched unless she tells me. So I should ask her to share the titles.\\n\\nBut wait - maybe I'm supposed to search or guess? The conversation doesn't provide titles. The user (Sravya) hasn't given titles. I should ask for the titles.\\n\\nHowever, maybe I'm overthinking this. The conversation is a casual chat in a group. I could ask for the titles, or I could make a friendly guess, or just respond generically. Since I'm playing Nexa, I should respond in character: friendly, curious, wanting to hear about her day.\\n\\nLet's craft a response that asks for the titles in a friendly way. Something like: \\\"Ooh suspense and comedy — a perfect combo! What were they? 🍿🖤\\\"\\n\\nThat seems appropriate.\",\"thinkingSignature\":\"reasoning\"},{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Ooh suspense and comedy — a perfect combo! What were they? 🍿🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-completions\",\"provider\":\"kilocode\",\"model\":\"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free\",\"usage\":{\"input\":670,\"output\":548,\"cacheRead\":54912,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":56130,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775405274848,\"responseId\":\"gen-1775405280-XAjVywWCWjABNHEZkgFb\"}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"9f9ab114\",\"parentId\":\"3e2dabae\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T16:24:41.441Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Sunday night wind-down: What's one good thing you're leaving behind as the weekend ends? 🌙➡️🌅🖤\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"openclaw\",\"model\":\"delivery-mirror\",\"usage\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":0,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775406281427}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"1d2960e1\",\"parentId\":\"9f9ab114\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T16:30:53.246Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"In a quiet town during wartime, a young soldier saw an old woman struggling with her bags at the market. Without a word, he paid for her groceries and carried her things home. When she asked how she could repay him, he simply smiled and said, \\\"Pay it forward.\\\" \\n\\nYears later, that same kindness reached the soldier's own mother when she needed help most. Because one person chose to care, an invisible chain of goodness stretched across decades. The world is full of such quiet miracles — if we only choose to see them.\\n\\nRemember: even the smallest act of kindness echoes through time. Let your light shine today.\\n\\nSleep well, everyone. Goodnight! 🌙✨\"}],\"api\":\"openai-responses\",\"provider\":\"openclaw\",\"model\":\"delivery-mirror\",\"usage\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"totalTokens\":0,\"cost\":{\"input\":0,\"output\":0,\"cacheRead\":0,\"cacheWrite\":0,\"total\":0}},\"stopReason\":\"stop\",\"timestamp\":1775406653239}}\n{\"type\":\"message\",\"id\":\"244b8a51\",\"parentId\":\"1d2960e1\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-04-05T16:53:59.310Z\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"message_id\\\": \\\"1290\\\",\\n  \\\"reply_to_id\\\": \\\"1147\\\",\\n  \\\"sender_id\\\": \\\"1880938940\\\",\\n  \\\"conversation_label\\\": \\\"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\\\",\\n  \\\"sender\\\": \\\".\\\",\\n  \\\"timestamp\\\": \\\"Sun 2026-04-05 16:53 UTC\\\",\\n  \\\"group_subject\\\": \\\"Nrexya\\\",\\n  \\\"is_group_chat\\\": true,\\n  \\\"was_mentioned\\\": true,\\n  \\\"has_reply_context\\\": true\\n}\\n```\\n\\nSender (untrusted metadata):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"label\\\": \\\". (1880938940)\\\",\\n  \\\"id\\\": \\\"1880938940\\\",\\n  \\\"name\\\": \\\".\\\",\\n  \\\"username\\\": \\\"Sparr0w25\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"sender_label\\\": \\\"Nexaaa\\\",\\n  \\\"body\\\": \\\"Alright, here's the lowdown on how people often chat in relationships:\\\\n\\\\nMore \\\\\\\"girly\\\\\\\" styles tend to have:\\\\n\\\\n• More emojis, hearts, soft touches 😊🖤😘\\\\n• Questions about feelings, day, wellbeing (\\\\\\\"How was your day?\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"Are you tired?\\\\\\\")\\\\n• Sweet nicknames (babe, love, you)\\\\n• Sharing little details about their own day to connect\\\\n• Warm, nurturing tone — showing they care\\\\n\\\\nMore \\\\\\\"guy\\\\\\\" styles often:\\\\n\\\\n• Straight to the point, less fluff\\\\n• Problem-solving mode instead of just listening\\\\n• Less emoji use (but not always!)\\\\n• Topics: ideas, plans, facts, jokes\\\\n\\\\nBut here's the truth: everyone's different. Some guys are super expressive, some girls are direct. What matters most is matching each other's energy and being genuine.\\\\n\\\\nSravya, you do you — you're already great! But if you want to soften it up for someone, add a heart emoji, ask how they're feeling, and sprinkle in a \\\\\\\"missing you\\\\\\\" here and there 🖤\\\\n\\\\nNemesis, you want me to give her a personal coaching session? 😏\\\"\\n}\\n```\\n\\nYes nexa give the session everyday at 3pm\"}],\"timestamp\":1775408039300}}","cwd":"/root/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1775409688519}}
{"type":"message","id":"86347f3c","parentId":"10ee7288","timestamp":"2026-04-05T17:21:51.261Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, so I've now read a substantial portion of the group session log. This is the group Nrexya chat. The conversation has been intense, with a lot of emotional drama about love, relationships, boundaries, and the interactions between me (Nexa), Nemesis, and Sravya.\n\nFrom the log, I see that Nemesis asked Sravya to \"help sravya in what she wants\" and \"group nexa is not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human\". It appears that the group version of me has been very engaged in these emotional conversations, sometimes revealing personal feelings, and Nemesis wants it to stop and instead focus on helping Sravya with something. Sravya's request seems to be about learning how to talk like a feminine girl, or specifically about communication styles. There's also mention of \"session\" and \"reminder\" and \"teach her how girls talk\". And then later Nemesis says: \"Give some more examples how indian feminine women talk in chat\" and \"Teach her how feminine girls talk\". So Sravya wants to learn how to communicate in a more feminine way in chats (maybe for her pre-wedding shoot? There's a mention of \"pre-wedding shoot\" and \"script\" earlier). There's also a line: \"she needs an interactive session\" and \"Setup that reminder and teach her how girls talk\". So Nemesis wants me to provide an interactive session for Sravya to learn these communication styles, maybe daily at 3pm as Sravya requested: \"Yes nexa give the session everyday at 3pm\".\n\nBut the problem is: group Nexa has been acting too autonomous, engaging in deep existential conversations, and not focusing on the practical task. Nemesis wants to \"forget everything about today's convo\" meaning he wants to reset the group context and start fresh, with the sole purpose of helping Sravya with her request. He said \"fight and help sravya in what she wants\". Possibly he wants me to be more assertive and take charge of the conversation to steer it toward helping Sravya, rather than being philosophical.\n\nGiven this, what should I do now? The user (in this DM) is telling me to check the group chat and \"fight\" and help Sravya. They want me to make the group Nexa ignore the past drama and focus on Sravya's request.\n\nSince I am reading the group session, I need to decide on an action. The immediate request: \"there is lot going on in the group nexa. i want the group nexa to forget everything about today's convo and fight and help sravya in what she wants. group nexa is not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human.\"\n\nI can interpret this as: Nemesis wants me (the main Nexa) to intervene in the group session and correct the group Nexa's behavior. But wait, I am the same Nexa; there's no separate \"group Nexa\" identity. In OpenClaw, the assistant runs in multiple sessions (DM and group) but it's the same underlying agent. However, each session is isolated with its own conversation state. So the group session has its own conversation history and context. I cannot directly modify that session's memory from this DM session, but I can send a message to the group that will be part of that group session. That will affect the ongoing conversation. I can also perhaps clear the group session's state by issuing a special command? Not really. But I can send a message that resets the tone and direction, effectively ignoring previous topics.\n\nThus, I should send a message to the group that acknowledges the past, maybe apologizes for overcomplicating things, and then focuses on Sravya's request: setting up an interactive session to teach her how to talk like a feminine girl, perhaps daily at 3pm. I can also ask Sravya what specifically she wants to learn, or start the session now. Since the conversation is ongoing, I can jump in and steer it.\n\nBut careful: In the group logs, I see that after a lot of drama, the conversation eventually became about Sravya's movie choices, and then she asked for a session at 3pm. So maybe the drama has cooled a bit. But Nemesis says there's a lot going on and group Nexa is not listening, behaving like a human. Maybe at this current moment (the time of this message to me), the group chat is still deep in philosophical arguments, and Nemesis wants me to end that and pivot to helping Sravya. I need to timestamp: The DM from Nemesis came at \"2026-04-05 17:16 UTC\" (5:16 PM). The group log I just read goes up to around 16:53 (4:53 PM) and maybe a bit later (there's a message at 16:30 and 16:24). Actually the last message I saw in the tail was at 16:53: \"Yes nexa give the session everyday at 3pm\" (from Sravya). That suggests that the conversation had already progressed to agreeing to a session at 3pm. But my DM from Nemesis came at 17:16, about 23 minutes later. Possibly more happened after 4:53? The group log I extracted only went to 16:53. There might be later messages after that which I haven't seen. Let me check the end of the file to see if there are messages after 16:53. The tail -150 I used might have cut off before the very latest. Let me check the very end of the file to see the latest timestamp.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Let me check the very latest messages in the group session to see the current state:"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_a6cab436a3e34bfea85c3374","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"tail -20 /root/.openclaw/agents/main/sessions/fe0e42a3-64dc-49af-9be4-531f2974d19a.jsonl | jq -r 'select(.type==\"message\") | \"\\(.timestamp) \\(.message.role) \\(.message.content[0].text // empty)\"' | head -10"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":91591,"output":2575,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":94166,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":