ultiple cron jobs each with a different tip on different days, but that's messy.\n\nAlternatively, I can simply send a single tip now and tell Sravya to ask me anytime, and I'll provide tips. But Nemesis wants a reminder. Maybe he means a reminder for Sravya to ask me, not a daily tip. The phrase \"setup that reminder\" could mean set a cron that reminds Sravya to ask me for a session. But earlier: \"setup that reminder and teach her how girls talk\". So the reminder is to teach her. So perhaps he wants a daily reminder that triggers me to initiate an interactive session. That is complicated.\n\nGiven the complexity, I'll keep it simple: I'll create a cron that sends a daily tip message to the group. I'll make the tip message generic and include a few examples. I can use a script that reads from a tip file and rotates. But to expedite, I'll create a simple shell script that picks a tip from a file and uses the message tool to send it. The cron will call that script. But the cron payload in OpenClaw can run arbitrary commands via shell? The payload.kind can be \"agentTurn\" (which starts an agent) or \"systemEvent\"? There is also the ability to define custom commands? Looking at earlier cron jobs, they used agentTurn with message. That spawns an agent that runs a prompt. So I could create a cron that spawns an agent with a prompt to \"send a daily feminine communication tip to the Nrexya group\". The agent would then generate a tip and send it. That would be easy: I just define a cron with agentTurn and a message like: \"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/tips/feminine-tips.txt, pick one tip, and send it to the group -1003606834639 using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, message=tip).\" That would work.\n\nI can create a file with a list of tips. Then the cron agent will read and send one each day. To rotate, I'd need to track which tip was sent last. Could use a simple counter file. But maybe for now I can just have a fixed tip or a set of tips and the agent randomly picks one. That's easy.\n\nHowever, I need to be cautious about adding new cron jobs: the system already has 10 cron jobs; adding more is okay but I need to be careful about rate limits and token usage. But it's fine.\n\nBut before I do all that, I should respond to Nemesis's DM? Actually the user sent me a DM in this session: \"there is lot going on in the group nexa. i want the group nexa to forget everything about today's convo and fight and help sravya in what she wants. group nexa is not listening anymore and she is behaving like a human.\"\n\nI am now in a DM with Nemesis. I need to reply to this DM. The user is instructing me to change the group behavior. So I should acknowledge and then take action. I'll say something like: \"Got it. I'll reset group Nexa and focus on helping Sravya. Setting up daily tips now.\" Then I'll actually send a message to the group and maybe set up the cron.\n\nBut careful: According to instruction, I should not send a summary of what I did unless asked. But here the user is asking me to do something; I can reply with a brief acknowledgment and maybe a confirmation once done. That's not a summary of unrelated actions; it's a response to his request.\n\nSo my reply will be something like: \"On it. Resetting group behavior. Sending a fresh start message to the group and setting up daily tips for Sravya.\" Then I'll perform those actions.\n\nBut the user said \"forget everything about today's convo\". That might also mean I should not reference the past in my group message. So I'll craft a message that doesn't mention the drama.\n\nAlso, the phrase \"fight\" could mean \"fit\"? Or maybe \"and\" but I'll ignore \"fight\" and focus on helping.\n\nLet's design the group message:\n\nSubject: Starting fresh! 📚\n\n\"Hey Nrexya! Let's kick off a daily dose of communication tips to help us connect better. Here's today's tip:\n\n**Feminine Chat Energy**: Add warmth with emojis and small expressions of care. Instead of just 'OK', try 'Okay! 😊 That sounds lovely! 🖤' — it makes a huge difference!\n\nIf you'd like daily tips, let me know! And Sravya, this is especially for you — hope it helps! 💕\"\n\nSomething like that, positive, forward-looking.\n\nI could also ask Sravya directly: \"Sravya, would you like me to send a daily tip at 3pm?\" but as a group message.\n\nNow, about the cron: I'll create a cron job at 9:30 UTC (3pm IST). But need to verify timezone: The other cron jobs use expressions like \"0 1 * * *\" for 1am? Actually they use UTC times. In MEMORY.md, the good-morning cron is at \"7:30 AM IST\". That's 2:00 UTC? Wait, 7:30 IST = 2:00 UTC (since IST is UTC+5:30). The cron expression likely has tz set. Looking at cron list earlier, I didn't see timezone info. But I can set a cron with a tz field. Let's define:\n\nschedule: { kind: \"cron\", expr: \"30 9 * * *\", tz: \"Asia/Kolkata\" } for 3pm IST? Actually 3pm IST = 9:30 UTC? Let's compute: 3pm IST = 15:00 IST = 9:30 UTC (since UTC = IST - 5:30). So the cron expression in UTC would be \"30 9 * * *\". Or in IST timezone, expr \"0 15 * * *\" with tz \"Asia/Kolkata\". Either works. I'll use tz to make it clear.\n\nThe payload: agentTurn with message that reads tips file and sends one.\n\nBut I need to create the tips file first. I'll create a file /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt with several tips. The agent turn will need to pick one and send. It can read the file, split by lines, pick one randomly, then use message tool. That's doable.\n\nBut the agent turn message needs to be a prompt that instructs the agent to do that. I can format it like:\n\n\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt, pick a random line, then send it to the Nrexya group using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, message=picked_tip). Ensure the tip is formatted nicely with emojis where appropriate.\"\n\nI'll create that file with maybe 7-10 tips.\n\nSteps:\n1. Create feminine-tips.txt with content.\n2. Add