{"type":"message","id":"c06bde24","parentId":"637f9918","timestamp":"2026-04-05T17:24:17.844Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I need to create a cron job that runs daily at 3pm IST (9:30 UTC or 15:00 with tz). I'll use tz \"Asia/Kolkata\" and expr \"0 15 * * *\". The payload will be an agentTurn that reads that file, picks a random line, and sends it to the group.\n\nBut to pick a random line, I need a small script. I can write a shell script that does:\n\n`shuf -n 1 /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt` gives a random line.\n\nThen I need to send that as a message to the group. I can use the `message` tool from within the agent turn. But the agent turn is just a prompt to the LLM. I can instruct the LLM to read the file and send. But random selection would require deterministic output? Actually the agent will use LLM to generate, which is non-deterministic but okay. I could ask the agent to read the file and then pick any tip (maybe the first). But I'd prefer random to avoid daily repetition. I can incorporate randomness by asking the agent to \"choose a tip that feels right for today\" or \"pick one randomly\". Since the LLM can simulate randomness (though not perfect), it's fine.\n\nSo the payload message could be:\n\n\"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt. Pick one tip (any line). Then send it to the Nrexya group using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, message=<the tip formatted nicely>).\"\n\nBut I need to ensure it includes emojis and formatting. The tips file already has formatting. The agent should send it as is.\n\nNow, I need to define the cron job. Let's use `cron add`. I need to construct the job JSON.\n\nFirst, I'll test if I can manually send a message with that content via a quick agent spawn to ensure formatting works. But I can do that later; the cron job will handle it.\n\nI'll create the cron now:\n\n- name: \"feminine-tip-daily\"\n- schedule: { kind: \"cron\", expr: \"0 15 * * *\", tz: \"Asia/Kolkata\" }\n- payload: { kind: \"agentTurn\", message: \"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt. Choose one tip (any). Send it to the Nrexya group using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, message=your_picked_tip).\" }\n- sessionTarget: maybe \"isolated\" (default for agentTurn). The message will be sent from the agent's context; it should be able to use the message tool, which will route to the main gateway. That should work.\n\nBut I also need to ensure the agent has the necessary permissions to read the file and send messages. Since it's running as the same OpenClaw instance, it should have access to the same tools (message, read). So okay.\n\nNow, after adding the cron, I'll also send an initial group message now to kick things off. That will be a separate message tool call.\n\nNow, the DM reply to Nemesis: I'll send a concise acknowledgment and then execute these actions. However, I need to perform the actions after I reply? I can call message tool for group and cron add before or after sending DM reply. I should do it all within this turn: I'll first call cron add, then send group message, then send DM reply to Nemesis confirming.\n\nBut the DM reply is the main response to the user. Since I'm in a DM session, if I send a message to the group, that's a separate tool call, not part of my DM reply. That's fine; I can do multiple tool calls in one turn before sending my DM reply? Actually the flow: I receive a message from Nemesis in DM. I need to respond. I can also perform other actions as part of my response. I'll call the tools (cron add, message for group) and then after they complete, I'll send my DM reply. That seems logical.\n\nHowever, the order: The DM reply is the final output of this assistant turn. I can include tool outputs before it? The assistant typically returns a response that might include both tool calls and a final message. But I can issue tool calls and then produce a response. That's fine. I'll do:\n\n- call cron add\n- call message for group (send initial tip message)\n- then send my final response to Nemesis\n\nBut note: the `message` tool for group will send a message to the group from the assistant. That's fine; it's part of the actions.\n\nNow, let's construct the cron add request. I need to use the cron tool.\n\nThe cron schema: job object with schedule, payload, [delivery], [sessionTarget], [name], [enabled].\n\nThe schedule: { kind: \"cron\", expr: \"0 15 * * *\", tz: \"Asia/Kolkata\" }\n\nThe payload: { kind: \"agentTurn\", message: \"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt. Choose one tip (any). Send it to the Nrexya group using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, message=your_picked_tip).\" }\n\nI'll set sessionTarget to \"isolated\" (default). Maybe I'd want it to run in an isolated session so it doesn't interfere.\n\nI'll name it: \"feminine-tip-daily\"\n\nNow, I'll execute cron add.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_1f21256d509f498a976403b8","name":"cron","arguments":{"action":"add","job":{"name":"feminine-tip-daily","enabled":true,"schedule":{"kind":"cron","expr":"0 15 * * *","tz":"Asia/Kolkata"},"payload":{"kind":"agentTurn","message":"Read /root/.openclaw/workspace/feminine-tips.txt. Choose one tip (any). Send it to the Nrexya group using message(action=send, channel=telegram, target=-1003606834639, message=your_picked_tip).","model":"kilocode/stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","sessionTarget":"isolated"}}}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"stepfun/step-3.5-flash:free","usage":{"input":107761,"output":2606,"cacheRead":256,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":110623,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1775409834815,"responseId":"gen-1775409835-Cm4yWs3MKWAvqBF7VuuR"}}
